The paper discusses community detection in large networks using content and link information. This topic falls under the scope of several arXiv CS sub-categories, including social and information networks (cs.SI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and statistical learning (cs.ST). However, given the emphasis on community detection and network analysis, cs.SI and cs.SD (software engineering and programming) are the most likely categories.
